@Chaldon-hl6yk The foundation of Veliky Novgorod (Novgorod Velikiy) is dated by archaeologists to the 9th–10th centuries, although the city is first mentioned in chronicles in 862.
Kyiv was founded in the late 5th–6th centuries AD as a Slavic settlement, which later developed into a political center of the Polyan. The official date of the foundation of the city is considered to be 482.

